```json
{
"application": "MILC",
"software": [
"KS_HISQ_SPEC",
"QUDA",
"Python 3.7.0",
"Anaconda 5.3.0",
"jsrun",
"sed"
],
"resources": [
"Summit supercomputer",
"GPFS filesystem",
"GPU-CPU nodes",
"MPI",
"OpenMP"
],
"libraries": [
"MPI",
"OpenMP",
"QUDA"
],
"environment_variables": [
"OMP_NUM_THREADS",
"QUDA_RESOURCE_PATH",
"KS_HISQ_SPEC"
],
"configuration_files": [
"milc_to_scidac.in",
"milc_to_scidac.input"
],
"output_files": [
"/gpfs/alpine/proj-shared/lgt100/c51/x_files/project_2/production/${ens_abbr}_${stream}/log/${ens_long}${stream}.${no}.log"
],
"input_files": [
"/gpfs/alpine/proj-shared/lgt100/c51/x_files/project_2/production/${ens_abbr}_${stream}/cfgs/${ens_long}${stream}.$no"
],
"other_details": [
"The script uses the MILC lattice gauge theory code to convert configurations from a MILC format to a SciDAC format.",
"The script runs on the Summit supercomputer and uses the GPU-CPU nodes.",

"The script uses the sed command to modify the configuration files."
]
}
```
